Title: 69301 - VM - Participation - Voter Participation Add/Maintain

Step Action:

- Have an existing Active Voter
Access the EMS system

Step Action: Click on the "Actions" ellipsis next to the existing voter

The Add Participation page is displayed and the following fields are present in this order:

 - Election Date (required field)

 - Election Name (Required field)

 - Party (Primary Only)

 - Method of Request (required dropdown: choices to be Election Day, Absentee, UOCAVA, Vote Center)

*Provisional Status Reason (Optional)

Step Action: Click "CREATE"

Step Action: Click "Ok"

All Participation History actions will be displayed here:
- Add
- Update
- Delete

Title: EMS - VM - Voter Search

Step Action: Open the application and login as county user and navigate to VM Module
Step Expected: VM home page is displayed

Step Action: Click on the Voter button
Step Expected: Voter Search page is displayed

Step Action: Select the search context: State or County from the County or State Search Selector dropdown.
Step Expected: User can select State or County. If State is selected, the search queries the entire state; if County is selected, it filters by county.

Step Action:
Fill in one or more search fields: 
 - Last Name 
 - First Name 
 - Date of Birth 
 - Driver's License/State ID 
 - SSN 
 - Street No. 
 - Street Name 
 - Apt/Unit No. 
 - City 
 - Zip Code 
 - Voter Status
Step Expected: Fields are filled with appropriate search criteria.

Step Action: Optionally, use wildcard search in any of the fields (e.g., %Jones, Jo%, %DES%).
Step Expected: Wildcard characters are used and partial matches are expected (e.g., %Jones returns "Jones," "Johnson").

Step Action: Click on the Search button.
Step Expected: The system processes the search query and displays results based on the entered search criteria.

Step Action: Review the search results displayed in the results grid.
Step Expected:
The following details should be displayed for each voter: 
 - Last Name 
 - First Name 
 - Date of Birth 
 - Street Name 
 - City 
 - Zip Code 
 - Voter Status 
 - County (when logged in as a Region user) 
 - Precinct

Step Action: If search results are paginated, use the pagination controls to navigate between pages (e.g., Next, Previous).
Step Expected: Pagination should work, allowing users to navigate through multiple pages of search results.

Step Action: Click the Manage option in the Actions menu next to any voter.
Step Expected: Clicking Manage opens the voter details screen for viewing voter information.

Step Action: Optionally, click Reset to clear all search fields.
Step Expected: The search form should reset, clearing all previously entered search criteria.

Title: VM-Ballot Add/Maintain UOCAVA/E&D Status

Step Action: Navigate to the "Voter" section and search for a voter
Step Expected: The user is able to search and select the voter successfully.

Step Action: On the voter information page, verify the "Absentee" tab is visible and accessible
Step Expected: The "Absentee Ballot" tab is displayed and accessible.

Step Action: Verify the "Add/Maintain UOCAVA/Permanent Absentee Status" button is visible under the "Absentee" tab
Step Expected: The button is clearly labeled as "Add/Maintain UOCAVA/Permanent Absentee Status" under the "Absentee Ballot" tab.

Step Action: Click the "Add/Maintain UOCAVA/Permanent Absentee Status" button
Step Expected: The user is navigated to a dedicated page for managing absentee status.

Step Action: Verify the stand-alone page is displayed with the voter card at the top
Step Expected: The page displays the voter card at the top.

Step Action: Verify the input fields on the page: - Annual Absentee Status (Dropdown) - Annual Absentee Status Reason (Dropdown) - UOCAVA Start Date (Date Picker) - UOCAVA End Date (Date Picker) - Ballot Mailing Address Checkbox (Conditional) - Mail Forwarding Address (Enabled for UOCAVA/FPCA)
Step Expected: All input fields are displayed correctly and are functional based on selection logic.

Step Action: Select "UOCAVA/FPCA" and verify the options in "Annual Absentee Status Reason" dropdown
Step Expected: The dropdown shows only: "Citizen Residing Overseas," "Member of Uniformed Services," "Spouse/Dependent of Uniformed Services Member."

Step Action: Select "Annual Application" and verify the options in "Annual Absentee Status Reason" dropdown
Step Expected: The dropdown shows only: "65 Years of Age or Older," "Disability," "Expected to Give Birth."

Step Action: Select "Annual Application" and check the Ballot Mailing Address checkbox
Step Expected: The system autofills the ballot mailing address with the voter’s registered address and locks the fields for editing.

Step Action: Uncheck the Ballot Mailing Address checkbox and verify the mailing address fields are editable
Step Expected: The mailing address fields become editable after unchecking the checkbox.

Step Action: Select "UOCAVA/FPCA" and verify the Mail Forwarding Address fields are enabled
Step Expected: The Mail Forwarding Address fields are enabled for input when "UOCAVA/FPCA" is selected.

Step Action: Select UOCAVA/FPCA and verify that the "Preferred Method" dropdown displays "Mail," "Email," and "Fax"
Step Expected: The "Preferred Method" dropdown shows the options: Mail, Email, and Fax.

Step Action: Select "Annual Application" and verify that only "Mail" is available in the "Preferred Method" dropdown
Step Expected: The "Preferred Method" dropdown shows only "Mail."

Step Action: Verify error handling for missing required fields (e.g., missing status reason or start/end date)
Step Expected: An error message is displayed indicating the missing required fields.

Step Action: Verify error handling if "Annual/UOCAVA End Date" is earlier than "Annual/UOCAVA Start Date"
Step Expected: An error message prompts the user to correct the dates.

Step Action: Input valid data into all required fields and click the "Save" button
Step Expected: The system saves the data and updates the voter’s absentee status. The user is navigated back to the voter history page.

Step Action: Modify the absentee status and click "Save" to update
Step Expected: The system reflects the updated absentee status immediately after saving.

Step Action: Verify that the system tracks and records changes for audit purposes
Step Expected: The audit logs track the changes made to the absentee status with details like the date and the user who made the changes.

Step Action: Simulate an error during the save/update process
Step Expected: The system displays a relevant error message, and no data is saved until the issue is resolved.

Step Action: Verify that the "Add/Maintain UOCAVA/Permanent Absentee Status" button changes to "Add/Maintain UOCAVA/Annual Absentee" after saving/updating
Step Expected: The button is updated to "Add/Maintain UOCAVA/Annual Absentee" after saving or updating the status.

Precondition: There is a voter already register which status is not Cancelled
Log in as a County user

Step Expected: User is redirected to the Voter Management screen

Step Expected: User is redirected to the Voter Search screen

Step Expected: Searched voter is displayed in the voter search grid

Step Action: Click on the Actions menu of the voter and select the Update option
Step Expected: User is redirected to the Voter Registration screen

Step Action: Click on the Next button at the bottom of the screen
Step Expected: Prompt asking for confirmation to proceed with registration is displayed

Step Action: Click Yes on the Confirmation pop up to proceed with the registration process
Step Expected: User is redirected to the Review screen

Step Action: Check the Override check box next to the Status Reason field
Step Expected: Status and Status reason fields are enabled

Step Action: Enter the Status: Cancelled
Step Expected: Cancelled status is set in the Status field

Step Action: Select the Status Reason and verify Status Reason options include but are not limited to: Deceased, Felon, Duplicate Record, Mental Incompetence
Step Expected:
Status Reason options include: 
 Adjudged Incompetent to Vote, 
 Cancellation Due to Texas Online Change (Cancelled by State), 
Convicted Felon,
Deceased, 
Disqualified Voter, 
Duplicate Cancel with No History by County, Expired FPCA, 
Failure to Respond to Notice of Investigation, Felon,  
FPCA - Deceased, 
Created by the System to Cancel an FPCA Voter That is a Duplicate, 
Created by the User to Indicate FPCA Cancellation at the FPCA Voters Request, 
FPCA Voters Permanent Record Cancelled by Strong Matched Merge, 
An FPCA Voter Was Cancelled by Reason 18 (Felony), 
An FPCA Voter Was Canceled by Reason 20 (Mental Incompetence), 
An FPCA Voter was Cancelled by Reason 24 (Non U.S. Citizen), 
General Duplicate Cancel by State, 
Mass Purge of Suspense Voters, 
Mental Incompetence, 
Merged Record Cancellation, 
Moved Out of County, 
Cancellation Due to Notice of Non-Citizen, 
Not a Citizen, Request by Voter, 
Response to Confirmation (Indicating Voter is Out of Country), 
Suspense to Cancelled, 
Voter Cancellation Due to Death and Was Reported by DMF

Step Action: Enter the Status Reason: Felon
Step Expected: Felon is set in the Status Reason field

Step Action: Select a Change Reason from the Change Reason Dropdown
Step Expected: Change reason selected is set ton the Change Reason Dropdown

Step Action: Click on the Update Registration button
Step Expected: User is redirected to the Final Screen page

Step Action: Wait more than one minute and click on the Refresh button in order to see the option to Print Letter enabled
Step Expected: Print Letter option under the Documents To Print section is enabled

Step Action: Check the Print Letter box
Step Expected: Print Letter box is selected

Step Action: Click on the Print Now button
Step Expected: Notice of Cancellation Letter is generated and downloaded for the user in PDF format
